h3. Summary

The text in a new or highlighted issue comment jumps around when hovered with mouse after Permalink is selected
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # open any issue with comments
 # open comments menu (under "...") and select "Permalink": page will be refreshed and you comment will be highlighted
 # start moving mouse on and off the comment

h3. Expected Results

Comment formatting is not affected by mouse hovering nor by any other mouse actions, so that I can read it without problems.
h3. Actual Results

Comment formatting changes when hover and unhover it with the mouse.
 
h3. Notes

Developer Tools showing below

.adg3 .issue-data-block:hover, .adg3 .issue-data-block .focused \{
background-color: #fafbfc;
border-left: 5px solid transparent;
}

If I remove the space character between .issue-data-block .focused, everything gets fixed:

.adg3 .issue-data-block:hover, .adg3 .issue-data-block.focused \{
background-color: #fafbfc;
border-left: 5px solid transparent;
}
